comments: Conley (UTA) places his hand momentarily on Poole's (GSW) hip before immediately removing his hand.
Green (GSW) is already in Conley's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs as he releases from the contact.
Green (GSW) is already in Conley's (UTA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Gobert (UTA) does not maintain verticality and makes contact with Poole's (GSW) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) is already in Thompson's (GSW) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Gobert (UTA) briefly grasps Thompson's (GSW) arm and marginal contact occurs as they briefly engage off ball.
Porter Jr. (GSW) brings his hand towards Bogdanovic's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Porter Jr. (GSW) brings his hand forward and makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm that causes Mitchell to lose control of the ball.  This contact then causes the ball to go out of bounds.
Possession is awarded to Utah.  Mitchell (UTA) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession should have been awarded to Golden State.
Thompson (GSW) is moving alongside Conley's (UTA) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Conley (UTA) goes to not through Green's (GSW) space and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Porter Jr. (GSW) and Bogdanovic (UTA) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Green (GSW) cleanly dislodges the ball from Gobert (UTA).
Green (GSW) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Utah.

As Poole (GSW) and O'Neale (UTA) engage for the rebound, Poole's hand makes some contact with O'Neale's head and the marginal contact occurs as Green (GSW) secures the rebound.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Gobert (UTA) jumps vertically as he defends the driving shot attempt, and the marginal contact is caused by Poole (GSW).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Gobert (UTA) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Golden State.
Conley (UTA) commits a take foul on Poole (GSW).
Gobert (UTA) and Green (GSW) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
O'Neale (UTA) commits a take foul on Green (GSW).
Payton II (GSW) dislodges Gobert (UTA) from his legally obtained rebounding position.
O'Neale (UTA) attempts to commit a take foul on Green (GSW) and the contact is marginal.
